      "description": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Educational Pathways International (EPI) is a foundation that offers a Four-year Scholarship to Brilliant but Needy Students to enable them pursue their University Education in their respective Countries.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Eligibility</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Scholarship is open to all Ghanaian students in their 1st &amp; 2nd, who are Brilliant but Needy Students of KNUST and who are pursuing a full-time REGULAR programme.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The minimum grade for prospective continuing student applicants must be at least a Second Class Upper (CWA of 67 and above). First-year applicants should have a WASSCE result /aggregate of at least Nine (9).</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>All prospective applicants are to include the following documents in their applications:</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n<li>Admission Letter</li>\n<li>Acceptance Letter</li>\n<li>WASSCE Certificate</li>\n<li>High School Transcripts or all Terminal reports.</li>\n<li>Recommendation letters and other awards or certificates (if any).</li>\n<li>Continuing student applicants should also add their complete University Academic Transcripts, (including current - Second Semester results).</li>\n<li>CONTINUING STUDENTS who are beneficiaries of other scholarships are not eligible to apply.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Application Forms can be downloaded via&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.knust.edu.gh/sites/default/files/2025-01/Educational%20Pathway%20Int.%20Application%20Form%202024-25.pdf\"><strong>(HERE!)</strong></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Please Note</h3>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n<li>All documents must be in a sealed envelope with the Applicantâ€™s name, programme and phone number boldly written on it.</li>\n<li>Submission of documents should be done at the Students Support and Financial Services (Room 19) at the Directorate of Student Affairs, J Harper Building.</li>\n<li>write-up should be typed in the font Times New Roman, size 12 and double-spaced.</li>\n<li>No Application will be accepted after the deadline. Only shortlisted applicants will be called for an interview.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">For any further enquiries, contact the Students Support and Financial Services Office.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Closing Date for Submission: Applications are to be submitted on or before&nbsp;<strong>Friday, 7th February 2025</strong>&nbsp;by 5:30pm for both the continuing and fresh students.</p>",
